If you add a couple of strategically placed &#39;interface&#39; keywords and delete
the &#39;protected, you get this :

public interface Node&lt;T&gt; {
  void process(T value);

    public static interface In&lt;T&gt; extends Node&lt;T&gt;
    {
      public void connectFrom(Node.Out &lt; ? super T &gt; node);
    }

    public static interface  Out&lt;T&gt; extends Node&lt;T&gt;
    {
      public void connectTo(Node.In &lt; ? extends T &gt; node);
    }
  }

